Now, for the fitness evaluation, we'll use a simple function that calculates the sum of all elements in an individual. The higher the sum, the better the fitness.

```cpp
// Fitness function
int fitness(std::vector<int>& indiv) {
    return std::accumulate(indiv.begin(), indiv.end(), 0);
}
